Privacy Policy for Oobada
Effective Date: 7/11/2025
Last Updated: 7/11/2025
Introduction
Oobada ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application Oobada (the "App").
Information We Collect
Information You Provide

Custom Language Data: The cipher languages you create, including character mappings and language names
User Preferences: App settings such as dark/light mode preferences
Subscription Information: Purchase and subscription status for premium features

Information Automatically Collected

Device Information: Device type, operating system version, and app version
Usage Analytics: Basic app usage statistics to improve functionality
Crash Reports: Technical data to identify and fix app issues

Information We Do NOT Collect

Your Messages: We never collect, store, or transmit the actual text you encrypt or decrypt
Personal Communications: Any messages you send via SMS or share with others
Contact Information: We do not access your contacts or phone numbers
Location Data: We do not collect or track your location

How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:

Provide App Functionality: Enable you to create, save, and manage custom languages
Maintain Your Preferences: Remember your app settings between sessions
Process Subscriptions: Manage premium feature access through Apple's App Store
Improve the App: Analyze usage patterns to enhance user experience
Customer Support: Respond to your inquiries and provide technical assistance
Legal Compliance: Meet applicable legal obligations

Data Storage and Security
Local Storage

Custom Languages: Stored locally on your device using iOS secure storage
App Preferences: Saved in your device's secure app sandbox
No Cloud Storage: Your cipher languages and messages are not stored on our servers

Security Measures

All data is encrypted using iOS standard encryption protocols
Your custom languages never leave your device unless you explicitly export them
No network transmission of sensitive cipher data
Secure handling of subscription data through Apple's systems

Data Sharing and Disclosure
We Do Not Sell Your Data
We never sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties.
Limited Sharing
We may share information only in these circumstances:

Apple App Store: Subscription status for premium feature management
Analytics Providers: Anonymized usage data to improve app performance
Legal Requirements: When required by law or to protect our rights
Business Transfers: In the event of a merger or acquisition (with the same privacy protections)

Your Control

Export/Import: You control when and with whom you share your custom languages
Message Sharing: You control all sharing of encrypted messages through your device's standard sharing features

Third-Party Services
Apple App Store

Subscription management and in-app purchases
Subject to Apple's Privacy Policy

Analytics Services

Anonymized usage statistics only
No personally identifiable information shared
Used solely for app improvement purposes

Children's Privacy
Oobada is designed to be family-friendly but is not specifically directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately.
Your Rights and Choices
Access and Control

View Data: Access your stored languages through the app interface
Delete Data: Remove languages individually or reset the app
Export Data: Share your languages with others at your discretion

Subscription Management

Manage Subscriptions: Through your Apple ID account settings
Cancel Anytime: Premium subscriptions can be cancelled through iOS Settings

Opt-Out Options

Analytics: Disable through iOS Privacy Settings > Analytics & Improvements
Personalized Ads: Control through iOS Settings > Privacy > Apple Advertising

Data Retention

Custom Languages: Retained until you delete them or uninstall the app
App Preferences: Retained until app deletion or manual reset
Subscription Data: Managed by Apple according to their policies
Analytics Data: Anonymized and retained for app improvement purposes only

International Users
Oobada is available worldwide. If you use the app outside the United States, your information may be transferred to and processed in the United States, where our service providers are located.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. When we make changes:

We will update the "Last Updated" date
Significant changes will be communicated through the app
Continued use of the app constitutes acceptance of changes

Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices:
Email: [your-email@domain.com]
Website: [your-website.com]
App Store: Search "Oobada" and use the developer contact option
California Privacy Rights
California residents have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):

Right to know what personal information is collected
Right to delete personal information
Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information (Note: We do not sell personal information)
Right to non-discrimination for exercising these rights

European Union Users
EU residents have rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):

Right of access to your personal data
Right to rectification of inaccurate data
Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")
Right to data portability
Right to object to processing
